				"Triangular numbers - odd numbers = shifted triangular numbers; 1, 3, 6, 10, 15, 21, ... - 1, 3, 5, 7, 9, 11,... = 0, 0, 1, 3, 6, 10,... - Xavier Acloque, Oct 31 2003 [Corrected by _Derek Orr_, May 05 2015]",
